<item>
  <title>PhD Defense</title>
  <link>https://ThomasLavigne.github.io/posts/2025/2025-24-06-PhD/</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 





<p>I successfully defended my PhD as part of a cotutelle program between Université du Luxembourg &amp; Arts et Métiers ParisTech - École Nationale Supérieure d’Arts et Métiers (i-biomec I2M – Institut de Mécanique et d’Ingénierie de Bordeaux)</p>
<p>My thesis, entitled <em>“Biomechanical Response of Human Skin: a Hierarchical Porous Media Framework”</em>, explored and evaluated a novel two-compartment porous model to capture the interaction between the mechanical behavior of soft tissues and microcirculatory response.</p>
<p>This journey was made possible thanks to the support and mentorship of my supervisors: Stéphane P.A. Bordas (FLSW), Pierre-Yves Rohan and Giuseppe Sciumè.</p>
<p>I’m also grateful to the jury and expert members for the rich and insightful discussions during the defence: Yohan Payan, Stéphane Avril, Christian Vincenot, Dr.-Ing. Silvia Budday, and Sébastien LAPORTE.</p>
<p>A special thank you as well to our collaborating laboratories -Laboratoire de Biologie Tissulaire et Ingénierie thérapeutique (LBTI), Institut FEMTO-ST, Laboratoire de Mécanique Paris-Saclay)- whose contributions, especially on the experimental side, were essential.</p>
<p>Heartfelt thanks to the volunteers who participated in the experimental cohorts and to all the individuals who contributed to this PhD.</p>
<p>Finally, I am honoured to have been proposed for the Pierre Béziers prize (ENSAM), Excellent Thesis Award (University of Luxembourg), the FNR Outstanding PhD Thesis, and the pre-selection for Prix Tarrach of <em>Les Amis du Luxembourg</em>.</p>
<p>This work was supported by the Luxembourg National Research Fund (FNR) under grant n° 17013182.</p>
<p>On to the next chapter!</p>
<p>#Biomechanics #PorousMedia #SoftTissues #Microcirculation #CotutellePhD</p>
