<item>
  <title>Visiting Brainiacs laboratory at FAU</title>
  <link>https://ThomasLavigne.github.io/posts/2024/2024-12-12-Erlangen/</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 





<p>Thanks to collaborations with S. Budday, we had the distinct opportunity to spend a productive week visiting the new, state-of-the-art laboratory of the <a href="https://www.lkm.tf.fau.eu/research/">brainiacs</a> research team at the University of Erlangen-Nuremberg (FAU). This highly collaborative visit allowed us to be warmly received by the group and gain in-depth exposure to their advanced work in brain experimentation and computational modeling. The trip served to strengthen research ties and provided invaluable insights into cutting-edge methodologies for both the physical study and the numerical simulation of complex brain mechanics.</p>
<p>We’re excited about the possibility of reconducting this initiative in the future!</p>
